# 13 — Server: `loop_n` and `loop_until_sentinel` (literal only)

**Status:** complete  
**Dependencies:** 11, 10

## Objective
**Loop workflows** with **one job per iteration** ... `loop_n` creates N jobs upfront; `loop_until_sentinel` creates jobs dynamically until worker reports sentinel matched ...

## Scope (in)
- POST /sessions accepts loop_n and loop_until_sentinel with params per API_OVERVIEW.
- v1 sentinel: literal substring only; case-sensitive default; document in server config/README.
- Worker signals via task_complete sentinel_reached; document in OpenAPI; server stops enqueuing.

## Acceptance
- Tests: loop_n exhausts N jobs; sentinel stops after k; max guard for unbounded sentinel (config).

--- IMPLEMENTATION SUMMARY ---

1) Migration `crates/server/migrations/20250320150000_jobs_queue_ordinal.sql`
   - ADD COLUMN jobs.queue_ordinal INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
   - Rationale: batch INSERT of loop_n jobs can share identical created_at; global pull uses ORDER BY created_at, queue_ordinal, id for stable iteration order.

2) ServerConfig (`crates/server/src/config.rs`)
   - loop_until_sentinel_max_iterations: u32, env LOOP_UNTIL_SENTINEL_MAX_ITERATIONS, default 500, .max(1) at load.

3) POST /sessions (`crates/server/src/sessions.rs`)
   - Workflows allowed: chat | loop_n | loop_until_sentinel
   - loop_n: params.n required positive i64, capped 1..=10000; N jobs with task_input { prompt, iteration, iteration_total }, queue_ordinal 1..=N
   - loop_until_sentinel: params.sentinel non-empty, max len 8192; one job { prompt, iteration: 1 }, queue_ordinal 1
   - Chat follow-up INSERT uses subquery COALESCE(MAX(queue_ordinal),0)+1 for ordering

4) POST /workers/tasks/:id/complete (`crates/server/src/worker_tasks.rs`)
   - Pull ordering: ORDER BY created_at, queue_ordinal, id (assigned reuse + pending claim CTE)
   - On failed job for loop_n | loop_until_sentinel: cancel remaining pending jobs with [CANCELLED_SESSION_FAILED]
   - loop_until_sentinel success: count completed jobs; if NOT sentinel_reached AND count < max → INSERT next pending job with task_input { prompt, iteration: count+1 }, queue_ordinal = MAX+1; session running if enqueued else completed
   - loop_n success: if any job pending|assigned → session running; else completed
   - chat unchanged (running on success); other workflows default completed on success

5) OpenAPI (`crates/server/openapi.yaml`)
   - TaskCompleteRequest.sentinel_reached description expanded for loop_until_sentinel behavior.

